# Unfixed glibc (libc6) CVEs in the gcr.io/distroless/cc-debian12 base image.
# Debian has classified all four `<no-dsa>` ("Minor issue") for bookworm —
# no security-advisory fix is planned, so no base-image update resolves them:
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-6238
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5928
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5450
#   https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2026-5435
# All four affect deprecated debugging-only resolver functions
# (ns_printrrf/ns_printrr/fp_nquery) or scanf/%mc and ungetwc edge cases this
# workspace's binaries do not exercise. `exp:` forces a revisit rather than
# relying on someone rereading this comment — re-check the Debian tracker
# links above when the gate reactivates on expiry.
CVE-2026-6238 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2026-5928 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2026-5450 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2026-5435 exp:2027-01-02

# reusable-trivy.yml builds a SARIF report, and aquasecurity/trivy-action
# unsets --severity entirely whenever format=sarif (to report every
# severity into code scanning), so the fail-closed image gate actually
# evaluates LOW findings too, not just HIGH/CRITICAL. The four CVEs above
# were the only ones visible under the severity filter this .trivyignore
# was first written against; these are the rest, all LOW, all rejected as
# non-issues by the relevant upstream or Debian:
#   CVE-2022-27943 (gcc-12-base/libgcc-s1/libgomp1/libstdc++6, gcc-12):
#     Debian: "Negligible security impact" (gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/105039)
#   CVE-2010-4756, CVE-2018-20796, CVE-2019-1010022..1010025, CVE-2019-9192
#   (libc6, glibc): all "Not treated as a security issue by upstream" per
#     glibc's own security-exceptions policy
#   CVE-2025-27587 (libssl3, openssl): "Not considered a vulnerability by
#     OpenSSL upstream" (openssl/openssl#24253)
CVE-2022-27943 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2010-4756 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2018-20796 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2019-1010022 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2019-1010023 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2019-1010024 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2019-1010025 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2019-9192 exp:2027-01-02
CVE-2025-27587 exp:2027-01-02

# CVE-2026-42767 (libssl3, openssl): Debian bookworm <no-dsa> but "can be
# fixed in next update" (unlike the entries above, upstream already shipped
# a fix in openssl-3.0.21; Debian just has not backported it into a
# security update yet). Shorter expiry since a point-release fix is
# plausible sooner than the others.
CVE-2026-42767 exp:2026-10-01
